<section class="feature_sections" id="hero">
	<div class="row">
		<div class="large-12 columns">
			<h1>The bulletin board, reinvented.</h1>
			<h3>Your space for creating and sharing things for people to read and do.</h3>
			<div class="visual_container">
				<%= image_tag "marketing/more_info/tile_wall_airbo2.png", "alt" => "Airbo Board" %>
				<p>Each communication, action, or link is turned into a special content format called a Tile.</p>
			</div>
		</div>
	</div>
</section>

<section class="feature_sections" id="tiles_detail">
	<div class="row">
		<div class="large-5 columns text_container">
			<h2>Tiles get attention</h2>
			<p>Where dense emails and posters go unread, Tiles capture attention using the perfect mix of consumer tools people love. </p>
			<ul>
				<li class="callout list_1"><p><span>Visual communication</span> Imagery grabs attention like today’s fastest growing consumer tools Pinterest and Instagram.</p></li>
				<li class="callout list_2"><p><span>Short content</span> Easy to read, like a text or Twitter message. Split content across Tiles for complex topics.</p></li>
				<li class="callout list_3"><p><span>Interactive</span> Users earn points for answering questions and taking actions. It’s a moment of delight that keeps people coming back.</p></li>
				<li class="list_4"><p><span>Links</span>Help aggregate content in a format that's easy to scan and points people to more information like videos or other resources.</p></li>
				<li class="list_5"><p><span>Ephemeral</span> Tiles are on the Board for a short time, creating a sense of urgency that other mediums lack.</p></li>
				<li class="list_6"><p><span>Modern Design</span> Built to optimize user experience. When a user completes a Tile, it disappears and the next Tile automatically loads.</p></li>
			</ul>
		</div>
		<div class="large-7 columns visual_container">
			<%= image_tag "marketing/more_info/tile.png", "alt" => "HEngage tile", "class" => "tile" %>
			<span class="list_1">1</span>
			<span class="list_2">2</span>
			<span class="list_3">3</span>
		</div>
	</div>
</section>


